{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd7eba0e94a3c4025d00", "type": "numerical", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 180, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "<p>The magnetic field at the centre of a wire loop formed by two semicircular wires of radii <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> carrying current <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> as per figure given below is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>\u03b1</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></math>. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>\u03b1</mi></math> is\u00a0_____. (Centre <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math> is common for all segments)</p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/a46f2cde-6b61-42cd-875b-aa07113600e9.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 182px;\"/>", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "3", "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/045a49dc-e6d5-4cb3-8f86-5e20e42ef08a.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 186px;\"/></p><p>From the figure, it is evident that the magnetic field at\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>\u00a0due to the straight portion of the loop is zero, only the contributions from the circular parts survive.</p><p>Also, the direction of the magnetic field due to the circular loops can be determined by the right-hand corkscrew rule.</p><p>Hence, the net magnetic field at\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>O</mi></math>\u00a0can be calculated as follows:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>B</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>\u03bc</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mfrac><mi>\u03c0</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>\u2297</mo><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>\u03bc</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mfrac><mi>\u03c0</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>\u2297</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>\u03bc</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>\u03bc</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mi>i</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>\u2297</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>\u2297</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mn>3</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></msup><mo>\u2297</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Hence,\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>\u03b1</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "bucket": "Must Do Ques (JEE Main) - Any Difficulty", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ21964302", "subject": "Physics", "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9e"], "topics": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "65c4c0c01d30997d3436baff", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "numericalLowerLimit": 3, "numericalUpperLimit": 3, "classes": [], "microConcepts": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61602420ae6dd863a9d1d7d8", "6160241f1a832a8dea12fbf0", "616024236098c3dc0cc3e764", "61602422b42cfaef18219875", "616024227e2ba4496fdd4552", "61964c8c8d7ade9f02022966", "61c08987636555dc34527e11", "61e7bd70643383b6c26bfb1d", "61964c8e8811f774a40dd9f1", "62962123b040395dcc21a751", "629f3a9143c2c00ea1d2f857", "629109edc3391b7808eb05af", "61bb820fdb486fa25580e4bd", "629f390c27047111eccefe03", "64eb06c03118f713ecfef077", "66d5853aa75f05ee8564f568", "67921d601d5b5072da5e9a88", "67fdff4f378e1624ea7b6a03", "6809202a3a10446a207fded7"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}